remarks: "Camestres", one of the syllogisms of Aristotelian logic.  All ` ph ` is ` ps ` , and no ` ch ` is ` ps ` , therefore no ` ch ` is ` ph ` .  (In Aristotelian notation, AEE-2:  PaM and SeM therefore SeP.) (Contributed by David A. Wheeler, 28-Aug-2016.)  (Revised by David A. Wheeler, 2-Sep-2016.)
statement:
camestres.maj $e |- A. x ( ph -> ps ) $.
camestres.min $e |- A. x ( ch -> -. ps ) $.
camestres $p |- A. x ( ch -> -. ph ) $.
